What food is he on? Try a salmon flavor and omega 3’s!
@rooandrhaegar I was thinking some kind of fish oil would help a lot because it’s out of hand how much he sheds. What do you feed your dogs?

@bradytherescueshep we’ve fed them like everything 😭😂😭 I settled on @canidaepetfood because it’s made in America, grain free, and not owned by Purina lol we did taste of the wild but on consumer affairs it’s got a horrid rating, my vet told me not to use it, and this dude at the dog store told me his dog died eating it. So after research I changed. We had merrick before but it’s made by Purina and I don’t like Purina. Kipper are Orijen which is like golden dog food but beyond expensive. Our dogs like do not shed it’s amazing. Roo and Riley are on puppy food still but for Rhaegar I’m changing the flavors every month
@rooandrhaegar how much do you pay for what you’re using now per bag for adults?
I think $53 for Rhaegars food. But they have a company they make called @underthesunlb and it’s cheaper and still grain free!
What are you currently feeding?
I’ll look into it.. Purina One 🙄 is what he’s on now because it’s cheaper and I was trying to get his medicine cost down so I could pay for better food. @rooandrhaegar

@bradytherescueshep try under the sun!!! It’s way cheaper than Canidae and grain free and good quality! I’ve done like a gross amount of research on dog food 😂 but ya totally understand. I got hooked on $$$ dog food because I knew kipper had a veryyyyy short time and thought maybe it would give her an extra day or two. So I splurged on Orijen. But with three huge dogs I wasn’t going to pay $90 a bag.

@rooandrhaegar I bet! Your dogs probably eat like crazy being German shepherds and 2 of them are puppies on top of it! Poor Kipper, I never met her because it was before I started volunteering. But when I think about you two and what you probably went through it makes me so happy you had her for that time. I can’t imagine what would’ve happened to Brady (or Kipper) if anyone else would have adopted them/sheltered them.

@bradytherescueshep she was the best. She was literally born to be my dog. I don’t think they would have adopted her out to someone else once she got the second heart defect diagnosis. But I was OBSESSED with her and sorta stalked Joyce and katie through Kips surgery lol and when I came to finally adopt her after she recovered I was sobbing lol on our next team boss walk I’ll tell you how it all went down. But when you mentioned Brady’s struggle I felt such a gut feeling about you being his mom the way I was Kips

@rooandrhaegar I know, when you were talking about Kip it made me want to cry thinking about how that could be Brady some day.. she got the BEST last couple months it sounds like! They probably wouldn’t have given her to anyone else but you, it was meant to be!
